ly illustrated and supported by thorough maps, the entries on individual composers trace their steps through the practicalities of life and reveal to us the context of creativity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aComposersxHomes and hauntszEuropevGuidebooks. 0aMusic museumszEuropevGuidebooks. 7aTravel / Museums, Tours, Points of Interest.2bisacsh1 aSadie, Stanley, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030010750040uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018394840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300183948423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300183948/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY